Preheat your oven to 200°C. Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into 4 long strips then chop widthways into roughly 1cm pieces. Pop the aubergine pieces onto a large #baking tray{} (you may need to spread across two trays), drizzle with oil. Toss to coat then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until soft and golden, ~{20-25%minutes}, turning halfway.

Meanwhile bring a #saucepan{} of water up to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp} for the pasta. Chop the @olives{30} into small pieces. Quarter the @baby plum tomatoes{125}. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press). Drain and rinse the @brown lentils{1%can} in a #sieve{}. When boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{200} and cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}, pop back in the pan, drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Add the shallot to the pan and fry until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add in the garlic, @dried Italian herbs{1/2%tsp}, @sun-dried tomato paste{1}, @?sugar{pinch}, stir through and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Pour the @finely chopped tomatoes with basil{1}(finely chopped), @red wine stock paste{28}, lentils and @water{50} into the shallot pan, bring to the boil, stir to dissolve the stock pot. Simmer until starting to thicken, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, put the olives, half the plum tomatoes and half the parsley in a #small bowl{} along with the @olive oil{1.5%tbsp}. Season with @black pepper{} and stir together.

Add the remaining plum tomatoes and roasted aubergine to the sauce. Stir together and simmer for a further ~{3-4%minutes}, then taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Add the drained pasta and remaining parsley to the sauce and stir to combine. Divide among plates and top with a sprinkle of @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and a spoonful of salsa.

> This super speedy lentil bolognese is perfect for a midweek meal. The combination of
> Italian-style herbs, aubergine and black olives give the dish the rich flavour of
> bolognese. Our chefs have also included red wine stock to really amp up the flavour.
> Quick to make and even quicker to eat, this dish will be a winner with everyone
> around the table.